# KTP daily performance rollup — Tier 3 Project 1 follow-up
#
# Fires daily at 04:30 ET (after the 03:00 fleet restart + 04:00 demo
# organizer + 04:15 demo retention sweeps complete). Computes per-host
# trailing-7-day baselines from hlstatsx.ktp_telemetry_metrics and posts
# Discord alerts on hosts deviating ≥2σ from baseline.
#
# Three-tier severity (per TODO.md Tier 3 Project 1 follow-up spec):
#
#   WARN     yellow embed, no role-ping
#              per-host fps_p50 < (mean − 2σ)
#              OR per-host daily spike_total > (mean + 2σ)
#
#   CRITICAL red embed, no role-ping
#              ≥3 hosts WARN on the same day
#
#   CRITICAL red embed, ping @KTP Admin
#              fleet daily median fps_p50 < FLEET_CRITICAL_FPS (default 963)
#
# Excluded from WARN: NY:27019 (perpetual pingboost-4 canary, σ=0.12;
# would fire on any drop below ~999.7 fps; not a player-serving instance).
# See PERF_EXCLUDED_HOSTS in /etc/ktp/discord-relay.conf.
#
# 48-hour suppression on first deploy: launch with `--dry-run` for the
# first 2 daily fires (runs the rollup, writes to ktp_telemetry_baselines
# table, but does NOT POST to Discord). Operator eyeballs the output via
# the log + the table, then removes --dry-run from this cron once happy.
#
# Implementation:
#   /usr/local/bin/ktp-perf-rollup       — Python script (this repo: scripts/ktp-perf-rollup.py)
#   hlstatsx.ktp_telemetry_baselines     — forensic cache, schema in DDL inside script
#   PERF_ALERT_CHANNEL in /etc/ktp/discord-relay.conf — embed delivery channel
#
# Operator note: the underlying ktp_telemetry MySQL user needs:
#   GRANT SELECT ON hlstatsx.ktp_telemetry_metrics TO 'ktp_telemetry'@'localhost';
#   GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON hlstatsx.ktp_telemetry_baselines TO 'ktp_telemetry'@'localhost';
# The DELETE grant pre-authorizes future replay scenarios (e.g. backfilling
# a day's row after a config-correction rerun); not used by the steady-state
# script. The baselines table itself must be pre-created as root (script's
# CREATE IF NOT EXISTS is idempotent but requires CREATE privilege which
# the scoped user lacks; `ensure_baseline_schema` probes via SHOW TABLES
# first to skip the DDL on the steady-state path).

SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin
MAILTO=''

# 04:30 ET daily. Wraps the venv'd python — pymysql lives in the
# ktp-profile-aggregator venv (we share it rather than maintaining two).
# --dry-run for the first 48h post-deploy; remove after operator eyeball.
30 4 * * *   root  set -a; source /opt/ktp-profile-aggregator/.env; set +a; /opt/ktp-profile-aggregator/venv/bin/python /usr/local/bin/ktp-perf-rollup --dry-run --config /etc/ktp/discord-relay.conf >> /var/log/ktp-perf-rollup.log 2>&1
